✅ Vault Agent Injector – Post-Onboarding Validations

After your application is onboarded to Vault and deployed on OpenShift:

Ensure that the Vault Agent Injector is working as expected.

You are responsible for verifying that secrets are being injected and used correctly by your application.


📘 Refer to the official validation guide for steps:
👉 Post-Onboarding Validation Guide

> 🔍 This guide includes checks for sidecar injection, secret file rendering, environment variables, and token renewal.



If you encounter issues, contact the Vault support team with:

Pod name and namespace

Pod annotations used

Relevant logs from the vault-agent sidecar container